    "abstract": "<jats:title>Abstract</jats:title>\n                <jats:p>We developed a genome-wide transcriptomic clock for predicting chronological age using whole blood samples from 463 healthy individuals. Our findings reveal profound age acceleration, up to 24.47 years, under perturbed homeostasis in COVID-19 patients, which reverted to baseline upon recovery. This study demonstrates that the whole blood transcriptome can track reversible changes in biological age induced by stressors in real physiological time, suggesting a potential role for anti-aging interventions in disease management.</jats:p>",
